1.3 Plot proportion of cells from each batch

#make an empty dataframe
integratedproptable <- data.frame()

#make list of batches
batches <- levels(forebrain.integrated$batch)

#subset seurat object by batch, make prop table, and append to dataframe
for (x in 1:length(batches)){ 
  batchname <- subset(forebrain.integrated, subset = batch == batches[x]) #subsets object to only 1 batch
  y <- prop.table(table(Idents(batchname))) #makes the proportion table for that batch
  y <- as.data.frame(y) #converts table to data frame
  y <- dplyr::mutate(y, batch = batches[x]) #adds the "batch" column
  integratedproptable <- dplyr::bind_rows(integratedproptable, y) #puts batch table at the end table
}

#rename columns
colnames(integratedproptable) <- c("cluster", "proportion", "batch")

#get colors from integrated map
cols <- c('grey', 'grey64', 'mistyrose2', 'chartreuse1' , 'chocolate3', 'deepskyblue1', 
          'rosybrown3','gold1', 'orange1', 'sandybrown', 'coral', 'navajowhite1',

          'cyan4', 'blue1', 'darkturquoise', 'yellowgreen', 'mediumspringgreen', 'lightskyblue', 'royalblue1', 'green1', 'magenta1',
          'purple','lightcoral', 'orchid1', 'palevioletred1', 'darkviolet', 'maroon1', 
          'tomato1', 'slateblue1','red','burlywood2','olivedrab1')

#stores mitochondrial counts in $percent.mt and then subsets to remove cells with less than 200 genes and those in which >6% of transcript counts were derived from mitochondrial-encoded genes
allages.merged[["percent.mt"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(allages.merged, pattern = "^mt-") #adds column with percent.mt
allages.merged <- subset(allages.merged, subset = nFeature_RNA > 200 & percent.mt < 6) #subsets based on features/cell and percent mt


#LogNormalize normalizes the feature expression measurements for each cell by the total expression, multiplies this by a scale factor (10,000 by default), and log-transforms the result. Normalized values are stored in allsampleslist[[1]][["RNA"]]@data.
allages.merged <- NormalizeData(allages.merged, normalization.method = "LogNormalize", scale.factor = 10000)

#save merged object with new name
save(allages.merged, file = "allages.merged.RObj")

#find variable features (Seurat)
allages.merged <-FindVariableFeatures(object = allages.merged, selection.method = "vst", nfeatures = 2000)

#find variable features (SP)
require(MASS)
new.meanCVfit <- function(count.data, diffCV.cutoff=3, mean.min=.005, mean.max=1000, main.use="", do.plot=T) {
  
  # Format for the plot
  if (do.plot) par(mfrow=c(1,3), oma=c(0,0,2,0))
  
  # Calculate empirical mean, var and CV
  mean_emp <- apply(count.data, 1, mean)
  var_emp <- apply(count.data, 1, var)
  cv_emp <- sqrt(var_emp) / mean_emp
  
  # Fit gamma distribution to 'size factors' to build negative binomial
  a <- colSums(count.data)
  size_factor <- a/mean(a)
  fit <- fitdistr(size_factor, "Gamma")
  if (do.plot) {
    print(fit)
    hist(size_factor, 50, probability=TRUE, xlab="UMIs per cell / mean UMIs per cell", main=paste0("Size Factors & Gamma Fit (a=", round(fit$estimate[1], 2), ")"))
    curve(dgamma(x, shape=fit$estimate[1], rate=fit$estimate[2]),from=0, to=quantile(size_factor, 0.999), add=TRUE, col="red")
  }
  
  # Create null negative binomial distribution
  #   Gamma distributions of individual genes are just scaled versions. If X ~ Gamma(a,b)
  #   then cX ~ Gamma(a, b/c)
  a_i <- rep(fit$estimate[1], length(mean_emp))
  names(a_i) <- names(mean_emp)
  b_i <- fit$estimate[2] / mean_emp
  names(b_i) <- names(mean_emp)
  mean_NB <- a_i / b_i
  var_NB <- a_i*(1+b_i) / (b_i^2)
  cv_NB <- sqrt(var_NB)/mean_NB
  
  # Calculate difference in genes' CV and null CV
  diffCV = log(cv_emp) - log(cv_NB)
  if (do.plot) {
    hist(diffCV, 150, xlab="log(CVgene / CVnull)", main="Diff CV")
    abline(v=diffCV.cutoff, lty=2, col='red')
  }
  pass.cutoff <- names(diffCV)[which(diffCV > diffCV.cutoff & (mean_emp > mean.min & mean_emp < mean.max))]
  
  # Plot variable gene selection
  if (do.plot) {
    plot(mean_emp,cv_emp,pch=16,cex=0.5,col="black",xlab="Mean Counts",ylab="CV (counts)", log="xy", main = "Selection of Variable Genes")
    curve(sqrt(1/x), add=TRUE, col="red", log="xy", lty=2, lwd=2)
    or = order(mean_NB)
    lines(mean_NB[or], cv_NB[or], col="magenta", lwd=2)
    points(mean_emp[pass.cutoff], cv_emp[pass.cutoff], pch=16, cex=0.5, col='blue')
    title(main.use, outer=T)
  }
  
  # Return list of variable genes
  return(pass.cutoff)
}

load(file = "dpf6.RObj")
load(file = "dpf15.RObj")
load(file = "adult.RObj")

#reorder batches in dpf6
dpf6$batch <- factor(dpf6$batch, levels = c("6dpf_b0", "6dpf_b1", "6dpf_b2", "6dpf_b3", "6dpf_b4", "6dpf_b5", "6dpf_b6", "6dpf_b7", "6dpf_b8", "15dpf_b1", "15dpf_b2", "15dpf_b3", "15dpf_b4", "Adult_b1", "Adult_b2" ))

#plot dpf6
